        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The addition of the consumption volumes in the US in 2002 (from USGS, 2002 Pesticide use Maps) of the pesticides 1,3-D, abamectin, amitraz, benzyladenine, bromacil, buprofezin, butenoic acid, chloropicrin, chlorthal (DCPA), clethodim, clomazone, copper, cryolite, cyclanilide, dicloran (DCNA), dicofol, dimethipin , dodine, DSMA, emamectin, endosulfan, endothal, ethofumesate, fenbutatin oxide, flumetralin, flumic-lorac, flumioxazin, gibberelic acid, hexythiazox, isoxaflutole, kaolin, maleic hydrazide, mepiquat chloride, mesotrione, metaldehyde, methoxyfenozide, methyl bromide, MSMA, oil, oxytetracycline, prohexadione, propargite, pyridaben, quinclorac, quintozene (PCNB), sethoxydim, sodium chlorate, spinosad, streptomycin, sulfur, sulfuric acid, tebufenozide, terbacil, tralkoxydim, tribufos, triphenyltin (fentin), vinclozolin has been used to estimate the production volumes of unspecified pesticide in the world. For that, it has been extrapolated to a Global production mix using the ha of Arable land and Permanent crops of US versus the ha of Arable land and Permanent crops in the world in 2002 (1514/179 million ha; FAOSTAT).</productionVolumeComment>
